t depths of the modern “social Hell.” In this manner, Marx revised republican ideas of freedom in response to the rise of capitalism.Combining research on Marx’s interlocutors, textual scholarship, and forays into recent debates, Roberts traces the continuities linking Marx’s theory of capitalism to the tradition of republican political thought. He immerses the reader in socialist debates about the nature of commerce, the experience of labor, the power of bosses and managers, and the possibilities of political organization. Roberts rescues those debates from the past, and shows how they speak to ever-renewed concerns about political life in today’s world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCapitalismxPolitical aspects. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aCapital.  aCharles Fourier.  aDante.  aG. A. Cohen.  aInferno.  aKarl Marx.  aOwenism.  aPierre-Joseph Proudhon.  aRobert Owen.  aSaint-Simonians.  aakrasia.  aanarchy.  aassociation.  acapital accumulation.  acapitalism.  acapitalist exploitation.  acapitalist mode of production.  acollective force.  acommerce.  adomination.  aexpropriation.  aforce.  afraud.  alabor power.  alabor.  amarket society.  amoney.  aoverwork.  apolitical economy.  apolitical theory.  aprimitive accumulation.  arepublicanism.  aseparatism.  asocial Hell.  asocialism.  asurplus labor.  atreachery.  awages.  aworkers' movement.  aworking class.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063859208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106065910 cprintz978069118081640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400883707?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978140088370742